				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Why cant we have a back stab?<a name="66492"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 12 04 10:40 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">What about a back stab AA?</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Not actually a bad idea, IMO, but I would prefer something a bit more purely bard-like.  Not to mention that Rogues would hate the idea.  Emulating something directly that another class has that's class-defining for that class (Rogue Backstab), is probably not the best approach.
<br />

<br />
How about an ability based upon sound that would be a horrid screech of discordant auditory assault that would in turn cause an opponent's concentration to break and thereby causing their Armor Class to be cut by 35% for 20 seconds (maybe 30 seconds)?  Have a 3-5 minute re-use timer built into it.
<br />

<br />
The best thing about this is that it would help other melees as well.  Isn't that what made this class so great so long ago?  Utility and the ability to amplify the other players around us.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
