				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Any real rogue wouldn't give a d*mn so long as their DPS is still miles ahead of us.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
It might be logical to think that, but I can guarantee you that a lot or rogues would squeal like stuck pigs and I am not sure I wouldn't squeal too, if I was one.
<br />

<br />
We can claim a rogue heritage all we want and Sony can promote the notion, but in terms of how you utilize rogues and bards, they have almost nothing in common which means in terms of functionality, by design we complement each other - we do NOT overlap.  If you give bards backstab, it moves us a notch in the direction of what rogues are now.  Personally, I think most rogues want to maintain every bit of uniqueness and distinctiveness they can.  The main reason is, they're already lumped into a big pile known as &quot;melee DPS&quot; consisting of monks, rangers, and spare knights and warriors.  The ability to sting for big numbers on backstab is one of the very few things that distinguishes them from the rest of the melee herd.  Seeing some other class get any version of that at all would not be welcome.  And to be honest, it wouldn't do enough for us to be worth the uproar.</span></td>
