				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Why cant we have a back stab?<a name="66572"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 12 04 4:24 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Who the h*ll cares what ADnD's definition of a bard is, this is EQ.  One of EQ's biggest mistakes was to define sk, rangers, pallies, etc as a x + y class, and give them lower level versions of x or y.  They should have been their own class, with their own abilities with their own spells.  With the release of Velious, they realised this and defined them more, and gave them very class specific spells.
<br />

<br />
Asking for backstab is dumb, our contribution to the group doesn't come from swinging a weapon, it comes from out songs.  I'd like to see our OoW songs upgraded to useful levels, before any &quot;backstab&quot; ability is added.
<br />

<br />
I like the idea of the increase crit of group member, song.  I'd like to throw another idea out there.  A song that will increase the proc rate of the group.  This would be useful on raids, and in group.  I'd like to see an AA that would upgrade our fading memories to make it harder for mobs to see through it, or maybe just to include undead.  Our current OoW class specific aa's are just as good as this back stab idea.</span></td>
