				<td colspan="2"><span>If you want flashy damage, the bard is the wrong class for it.  Wizards are top in flashyness, with rouges and pallies (SU3 fun) following.  Bards are all about subtlety.  We help everything along without any one thing standing out (aside maybe from our pulling and resists).  
<br />

<br />
We add some DPS from Rizlona and damage shields, we add to defense with AC and resist songs, we increase mana, we help with mezzing, a little bit of everything.  I never hear someone say &quot;wow, we need that wizard, you see those crits?&quot;  BUt I do often hear &quot;man, this group ran so much smoother when we had the bard.&quot;
<br />

<br />
We smooth out the bumps, and we should be happy with our role.  
<br />

